  "invariants": [
    "USP_CurrentOverview materializes every requested shared source at most once per invocation.",
    "Every enabled shared consumer receives the same non-null SnapshotId.",
    "CapturedAtUtc and CompletedAtUtc describe each source separately; the snapshot is not transactionally atomic.",
    "A standalone consumer invocation materializes fresh local source data and never reuses an earlier parent snapshot.",
    "Input-buffer evidence is read only after request filtering and row limiting.",
    "A missing text payload is never presented as proof that an empty SQL value was executed.",
    "NOT_COLLECTED is an explicit omission state and does not by itself make the invocation partial.",
